.0, "avg_logprob": -0.06259911163993503, "compression_ratio": 1.694078947368421, "no_speech_prob": 2.708424630404327e-12}, {"id": 42, "seek": 12768, "start": 150.06, "end": 154.86, "text": " This translates ICN data names into time-sensitive networking reservations, which are guaranteed hardware", "tokens": [51484, 639, 28468, 14360, 45, 1412, 5288, 666, 565, 12, 82, 34465, 17985, 40222, 11, 597, 366, 18031, 8837, 51724], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.06259911163993503, "compression_ratio": 1.694078947368421, "no_speech_prob": 2.708424630404327e-12}, {"id": 43, "seek": 15486, "start": 154.86, "end": 157.20000000000002, "text": " paths across the network backbone.", "tokens": [50365, 14518, 2108, 264, 3209, 34889, 13, 50482], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1315753901446307, "compression_ratio": 1.603896103896104, "no_speech_prob": 3.383907737353198e-12}, {"id": 44, "seek": 15486, "start": 157.20000000000002, "end": 162.46, "text": " Fusing data names with time-sensitive networking creates zero-congestion hardware contracts for", "tokens": [50482, 479, 7981, 1412, 5288, 365, 565, 12, 82, 34465, 17985, 7829, 4018, 12, 40275, 31342, 8837, 13952, 337, 50745], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1315753901446307, "compression_ratio": 1.603896103896104, "no_speech_prob": 3.383907737353198e-12}, {"id": 45, "seek": 15486, "start": 162.46, "end": 168.8, "text": " critical data, a level of reliability that was previously impossible on standard Ethernet.", "tokens": [50745, 4924, 1412, 11, 257, 1496, 295, 24550, 300, 390, 8046, 6243, 322, 3832, 38636, 7129, 13, 51062], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1315753901446307, "compression_ratio": 1.603896103896104, "no_speech_prob": 3.383907737353198e-12}, {"id": 46, "seek": 15486, "start": 168.8, "end": 173.3, "text": " This architectural shift also changes how the network defends itself against distributed", "tokens": [51062, 639, 26621, 5513, 611, 2962, 577, 264, 3209, 1060, 2581, 2564, 1970, 12631, 51287], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1315753901446307, "compression_ratio": 1.603896103896104, "no_speech_prob": 3.383907737353198e-12}, {"id": 47, "seek": 15486, "start": 173.3, "end": 178.24, "text": " denial-of-service, or DDoS attacks, where massive floods of garbage traffic are used to", "tokens": [51287, 28754, 12, 2670, 12, 39279, 11, 420, 413, 7653, 50, 8122, 11, 689, 5994, 35536, 295, 14150, 6419, 366, 1143, 281, 51534], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1315753901446307, "compression_ratio": 1.603896103896104, "no_speech_prob": 3.383907737353198e-12}, {"id": 48, "seek": 15486, "start": 178.24, "end": 180.48000000000002, "text": " crash systems.", "tokens": [51534, 8252, 3652, 13, 51646], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1315753901446307, "compression_ratio": 1.603896103896104, "no_speech_prob": 3.383907737353198e-12}, {"id": 49, "seek": 15486, "start": 180.48000000000002, "end": 184.60000000000002, "text": " Memnet integrates the marine algorithm directly into the hardware of the router.", "tokens": [51646, 8731, 7129, 3572, 1024, 264, 20246, 9284, 3838, 666, 264, 8837, 295, 264, 22492, 13, 51852], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1315753901446307, "compression_ratio": 1.603896103896104, "no_speech_prob": 3.383907737353198e-12}, {"id": 50, "seek": 18460, "start": 184.6, "end": 191.1, "text": " It identifies anomalies in O1 constant time, performing detection at line-rate speeds.", "tokens": [50365, 467, 34597, 24769, 48872, 294, 422, 16, 5754, 565, 11, 10205, 17784, 412, 1622, 12, 4404, 16411, 13, 50690], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09693239302862258, "compression_ratio": 1.598639455782313, "no_speech_prob": 2.75107345758252e-12}, {"id": 51, "seek": 18460, "start": 191.1, "end": 195.78, "text": " Instead of heavy processing, the algorithm monitors traffic behavior by analyzing jitter,", "tokens": [50690, 7156, 295, 4676, 9007, 11, 264, 9284, 26518, 6419, 5223, 538, 23663, 361, 3904, 11, 50924], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09693239302862258, "compression_ratio": 1.598639455782313, "no_speech_prob": 2.75107345758252e-12}, {"id": 52, "seek": 18460, "start": 195.78, "end": 198.35999999999999, "text": " the timing deviations between packets.", "tokens": [50924, 264, 10822, 31219, 763, 1296, 30364, 13, 51053], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09693239302862258, "compression_ratio": 1.598639455782313, "no_speech_prob": 2.75107345758252e-12}, {"id": 53, "seek": 18460, "start": 198.35999999999999, "end": 202.07999999999998, "text": " A DDoS attack is a chaotic explosion of erratic jitter.", "tokens": [51053, 316, 413, 7653, 50, 2690, 307, 257, 27013, 15673, 295, 1189, 25198, 361, 3904, 13, 51239], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09693239302862258, "compression_ratio": 1.598639455782313, "no_speech_prob": 2.75107345758252e-12}, {"id": 54, "seek": 18460, "start": 202.07999999999998, "end": 206.2, "text": " The switch instantly drops these malicious packets into a background queue before they tax", "tokens": [51239, 440, 3679, 13518, 11438, 613, 33496, 30364, 666, 257, 3678, 18639, 949, 436, 3366, 51445], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09693239302862258, "compression_ratio": 1.598639455782313, "no_speech_prob": 2.75107345758252e-12}, {"id": 55, "seek": 18460, "start": 206.2, "end": 207.78, "text": " the system.", "tokens": [51445, 264, 1185, 13, 51524], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09693239302862258, "compression_ratio": 1.598639455782313, "no_speech_prob": 2.75107345758252e-12}, {"id": 56, "seek": 18460, "start": 207.78, "end": 212.2, "text": " Treating jitter as a behavioral signature allows the network to identify and neutralize threats", "tokens": [51524, 20298, 278, 361, 3904, 382, 257, 19124, 13397, 4045, 264, 3209, 281, 5876, 293, 10598, 1125, 14909, 51745], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09693239302862258, "compression_ratio": 1.598639455782313, "no_speech_prob": 2.75107345758252e-12}, {"id": 57, "seek": 21220, "start": 212.2, "end": 213.2, "text": " at the hardware level.", "tokens": [50365, 412, 264, 8837, 1496, 13, 50415], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11497579618941905, "compression_ratio": 1.4615384615384615, "no_speech_prob": 4.041997205689318e-12}, {"id": 58, "seek": 21220, "start": 213.2, "end": 219.7, "text": " This efficiency extends to edge devices through a power-aware strategy that utilizes multiple", "tokens": [50415, 639, 10493, 26448, 281, 4691, 5759, 807, 257, 1347, 12, 17074, 5206, 300, 4976, 5660, 3866, 50740], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11497579618941905, "compression_ratio": 1.4615384615384615, "no_speech_prob": 4.041997205689318e-12}, {"id": 59, "seek": 21220, "start": 219.7, "end": 220.7, "text": " radios.", "tokens": [50740, 2843, 2717, 13, 50790], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11497579618941905, "compression_ratio": 1.4615384615384615, "no_speech_prob": 4.041997205689318e-12}, {"id": 60, "seek": 21220, "start": 220.7, "end": 226.26, "text": " A sensor can stay in a low-power sleep state, using only a tiny LoRa radio to listen for", "tokens": [50790, 316, 10200, 393, 1754, 294, 257, 2295, 12, 9513, 2817, 1785, 11, 1228, 787, 257, 5870, 6130, 41873, 6477, 281, 2140, 337, 51068], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11497579618941905, "compression_ratio": 1.4615384615384615, "no_speech_prob": 4.041997205689318e-12}, {"id": 61, "seek": 21220, "start": 226.26, "end": 227.76, "text": " an interest ping.", "tokens": [51068, 364, 1179, 26151, 13, 51143], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11497579618941905, "compression_ratio": 1.4615384615384615, "no_speech_prob": 4.041997205689318e-12}, {"id": 62, "seek": 21220, "start": 227.76, "end": 232.26, "text": " It only wakes up its high-bandwidth Wi-Fi chip when there is a specific request for a heavy", "tokens": [51143, 467, 787, 29610, 493, 1080, 1090, 12, 4235, 21271, 14035, 12, 13229, 11409, 562, 456, 307, 257, 2685, 5308, 337, 257, 4676, 51368], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11497579618941905, "compression_ratio": 1.4615384615384615, "no_speech_prob": 4.041997205689318e-12}, {"id": 63, "seek": 23226, "start": 232.26, "end": 233.26, "text": " data payload.", "tokens": [50365, 1412, 30918, 13, 50415], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.07856409399359075, "compression_ratio": 1.6609589041095891, "no_speech_prob": 2.227365210674681e-12}, {"id": 64, "seek": 23226, "start": 233.26, "end": 238.72, "text": " To maintain security in these large-scale meshes, Memnet integrates a peer-to-peer reputation", "tokens": [50415, 1407, 6909, 3825, 294, 613, 2416, 12, 20033, 3813, 8076, 11, 8731, 7129, 3572, 1024, 257, 15108, 12, 1353, 12, 494, 260, 13061, 50688], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.07856409399359075, "compression_ratio": 1.6609589041095891, "no_speech_prob": 2.227365210674681e-12}, {"id": 65, "seek": 23226, "start": 238.72, "end": 241.7, "text": " system directly into the routing logic.", "tokens": [50688, 1185, 3838, 666, 264, 32722, 9952, 13, 50837], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.07856409399359075, "compression_ratio": 1.6609589041095891, "no_speech_prob": 2.227365210674681e-12}, {"id": 66, "seek": 23226, "start": 241.7, "end": 243.94, "text": " Routers constantly evaluate their neighbors.", "tokens": [50837, 497, 346, 433, 6460, 13059, 641, 12512, 13, 50949], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.07856409399359075, "compression_ratio": 1.6609589041095891, "no_speech_prob": 2.227365210674681e-12}, {"id": 67, "seek": 23226, "start": 243.94, "end": 249.01999999999998, "text": " If a node is identified as malicious or refuses to cooperate, the network lowers its reputation", "tokens": [50949, 759, 257, 9984, 307, 9234, 382, 33496, 420, 33222, 281, 26667, 11, 264, 3209, 44936, 1080, 13061, 51203], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.07856409399359075, "compression_ratio": 1.6609589041095891, "no_speech_prob": 2.227365210674681e-12}, {"id": 68, "seek": 23226, "start": 249.01999999999998, "end": 251.07999999999998, "text": " score and automatically avoids it.", "tokens": [51203, 6175, 293, 6772, 3641, 3742, 309, 13, 51306], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.07856409399359075, "compression_ratio": 1.6609589041095891, "no_speech_prob": 2.227365210674681e-12}, {"id": 69, "seek": 23226, "start": 251.07999999999998, "end": 256.52, "text": " Memnet transforms telecommunications from a system that blindly transmits bits into a semantic", "tokens": [51306, 8731, 7129, 35592, 4304, 25451, 24847, 490, 257, 1185, 300, 47744, 7715, 1208, 9239, 666, 257, 47982, 51578], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.07856409399359075, "compression_ratio": 1.6609589041095891, "no_speech_prob": 2.227365210674681e-12}, {"id": 70, "seek": 23226, "start": 256.52, "end": 260.26, "text": " substrate that natively prioritizes and authenticates information.", "tokens": [51578, 27585, 300, 8470, 356, 14846, 5660, 293, 12466, 1024, 1589, 13, 51765], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.07856409399359075, "compression_ratio": 1.6609589041095891, "no_speech_prob": 2.227365210674681e-12}, {"id": 71, "seek": 26026, "start": 260.26, "end": 265.64, "text": " This 6G infrastructure coordinates data based on its internal semantic value, allowing the", "tokens": [50365, 639, 1386, 38, 6896, 21056, 1412, 2361, 322, 1080, 6920, 47982, 2158, 11, 8293, 264, 50634], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19221567385124438, "compression_ratio": 1.2661290322580645, "no_speech_prob": 4.097173555289713e-12}, {"id": 72, "seek": 26026, "start": 265.64, "end": 269.09999999999997, "text": " internet to function as a globally distributed, self-aware memory.", "tokens": [50634, 4705, 281, 2445, 382, 257, 18958, 12631, 11, 2698, 12, 17074, 4675, 13, 50807], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19221567385124438, "compression_ratio": 1.2661290322580645, "no_speech_prob": 4.097173555289713e-12}], "language": "en"}